Docker + Spring Boot Demo 

This project demonstrates how to:

Create a simple Spring Boot application

Build it using Maven

Containerize it using Docker

Push it to Docker Hub

Run it on another machine

 Prerequisites

Make sure you have installed:

Java 21

Maven

Docker

Verify installations:

java -version
mvn -version
docker --version

 Step 1 ‚Äì Create Spring Boot Project

Generate a Spring Boot project using:

Maven

Java 21

Spring Web dependency

Project structure:

demo
 ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ src
 ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ pom.xml
 ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Dockerfile

 Step 2 ‚Äì Create Simple REST Controller

Create:

src/main/java/com/example/demo/HelloController.java

package com.example.demo;

import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;

@RestController
@RequestMapping("/")
public class HelloController {

    @GetMapping
    public String home() {
        return "Hello Docker + Spring Boot üöÄ";
    }
}

 Step 3 ‚Äì Run Application Locally (Without Docker)
mvn spring-boot:run


Open browser:

http://localhost:8080


Expected output:

Hello Docker + Spring Boot üöÄ


Stop application:

CTRL + C

 Step 4 ‚Äì Build JAR File
mvn clean package


After build, check:

target/demo-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar


Test JAR:

java -jar target/demo-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar


Open:

http://localhost:8080


Stop with:

CTRL + C

 Step 5 ‚Äì Create Dockerfile

Create a file named Dockerfile in project root:

FROM eclipse-temurin:21-jdk-jammy
WORKDIR /app
COPY target/demo-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar app.jar
EXPOSE 8080
ENTRYPOINT ["java","-jar","app.jar"]

 Step 6 ‚Äì Build Docker Image
docker build -t demo-app .


Verify:

docker images


You should see:

demo-app   latest

 Step 7 ‚Äì Run Docker Container
docker run -p 8080:8080 demo-app


Open:

http://localhost:8080


To run in background:

docker run -d -p 8080:8080 demo-app


Check running containers:

docker ps


Stop container:

docker stop <container_id>

 Step 8 ‚Äì Push Image to Docker Hub
1Ô∏è Login
docker login

2Ô∏è Tag Image

Replace yourusername with your Docker Hub username.

docker tag demo-app yourusername/demo-app:1.0

3Ô∏è Push
docker push yourusername/demo-app:1.0


Verify on Docker Hub website.

 Step 9 ‚Äì Run on Another Machine

On another system:

docker login
docker pull yourusername/demo-app:1.0
docker run -p 8080:8080 yourusername/demo-app:1.0


Open:

http://localhost:8080

‚ö† Common Issues & Fixes
Port Already Allocated

If you see:

Bind for 0.0.0.0:8080 failed


Use another port:

docker run -p 9090:8080 yourusername/demo-app:1.0


Then open:

http://localhost:9090

Image Not Found

If:

docker pull yourusername/demo-app:1.0
not found


Make sure you pushed the image correctly:

docker push yourusername/demo-app:1.0

 What This Project Demonstrates

Spring Boot REST API

Maven build lifecycle

Docker image creation

Container networking

Image distribution using Docker Hub